    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I've seen this before but I'm still -1 as I don't believe it is in the scope of pandas to resolve, nor do I think there would be a large enough consensus as to how to actually handle that type of header information (ex: should it be a string or dict return?)\r\n\r\nI've been wrong before so let's leave open to see what others think.\r\n\r\n> I currently have to read in the file once to grab the header\r\n\r\nIIUC you can just open a file handle, loop until you don't see comments to start and then simply pass that opened handle to `read_csv` (assuming your checks on comments have passed) to prevent having to close / open the file multiple times\r\n\r\n> For the love of science?\r\n\r\nDon't get me started"
  },
